name: Bruins
summary: The Boston Bruins have made a coaching change, firing Jim Montgomery after a disappointing start to the season. Montgomery was hired in 2022 and led the team to a franchise-record 54 wins, but the Bruins have struggled this season, and fan and media alike have called for Montgomery's job. The Bruins currently sit in last place in the NHL's Eastern Conference standings, and have been criticised for their poor defense and lack of scoring. Injuries to key players, such as Hampus Lindholm, as well as inconsistent goaltending from Jeremy Swayman have also contributed to the team's struggles. The Bruins are hoping that a change in leadership will help turn things around, but some have questioned whether the team's problems are more systemic, and may require more than just a coaching change to fix.

His retirement will undoubtedly leave a void in the sport, but his legacy will continue to inspire generations to come.
